item.title: A serious map problem
item.dc:creator: @usama299 usama299
item.description:
@usama299 wrote:

Spalterscape:

I had teh same problem, its because you have added some models in cache that overwrites the map models. Try backing up ur cache models, and delete the low numbered models like if you have 36.dat or 1546.dat etc etc. If that dosent work, try deleting all ur cache models after backing them up and see if it works. Mabye you have tried to add godwars? Thats how it happened to me lol, deleted them after i saw it and the problem was solved

When I added Godwars… Problems came…

EDIT: I removed the Godwars and It worked 100%! Thanks for advice =]

Read full topic

item.title: A serious map problem
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

Spalterscape:

I had teh same problem, its because you have added some models in cache that overwrites the map models. Try backing up ur cache models, and delete the low numbered models like if you have 36.dat or 1546.dat etc etc. If that dosent work, try deleting all ur cache models after backing them up and see if it works. Mabye you have tried to add godwars? Thats how it happened to me lol, deleted them after i saw it and the problem was solved

It should have nothing to do with “models”. If that’s happening, it means you have written over a portion of the flo.dat. Only way to fix is to find a cache that is unedited, and then add the models, etc you want.
